Overview
Three Paths Forward

We've put together three options based on where OneStop601 is today and where you want to go. Each option includes buy-now-pay-later integration (Afterpay, Klarna, Sezzle) so your customers can split payments at checkout — no matter which path you choose.

Our recommendation? Option 2. It gives you everything Shopify can't — full ownership, zero platform fees, a system built exactly for how you run your business — at a price point that makes sense for a growing operation. But all three are real options, and we're happy to walk through any of them.

Best for: Getting online fast with minimal investment. This upgrades your current Shopify store with a professional look, buy-now-pay-later options, and a better shopping experience. You keep using Shopify's existing tools for inventory and orders.

Limitations: You're still on Shopify — monthly platform fees ($39–$79/mo), transaction fees on every sale, and limited customization beyond what Shopify themes allow. No barcode scanning, no StockX integration, no custom admin tools.
